basRip2.name: basRip2
basRip2.contactinfo: Tech Support Broadband Access Systems 201 Forest Street Marlboro, MA 01752 U.S.A. 508-485-8200 support@basystems.com
basRip2.description: This module defines the MIB objects for a Broadband Access System IP Forwarding component.

RouteTag.name: RouteTag
RouteTag.description: the RouteTag type represents the contents of the Route Domain field in the packet header or route entry

basRip2GlobalsTable.name: basRip2GlobalsTable
basRip2GlobalsTable.description: A list of Route Server forwarding table distribution mechanism statistics.

basRip2GlobalRouteChanges.name: basRip2GlobalRouteChanges
basRip2GlobalRouteChanges.description: The number of route changes made to the IP Route Database by RIP. This does not include the refresh of a route's age.

basRip2GlobalQueries.name: basRip2GlobalQueries
basRip2GlobalQueries.description: The number of responses sent to RIP queries from other systems.

basRip2GlobalChassis.name: basRip2GlobalChassis
basRip2GlobalChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of the Route Server.

basRip2GlobalSlot.name: basRip2GlobalSlot
basRip2GlobalSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of the Route Server.

basRip2GlobalIf.name: basRip2GlobalIf
basRip2GlobalIf.description: The BAS interface ID of the Route Server.

basRip2GlobalLPort.name: basRip2GlobalLPort
basRip2GlobalLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfStatTable.name: basRip2IfStatTable
basRip2IfStatTable.description: A list of subnets which require separate status monitoring in RIP.

basRip2IfStatEntry.name: basRip2IfStatEntry
basRip2IfStatEntry.description: A Single Routing Domain in a single Subnet.

basRip2IfStatAddress.name: basRip2IfStatAddress
basRip2IfStatAddress.description: The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet. For unnumbered interfaces, the value 0.0.0.N, where the least significant 24 bits (N) is the ifIndex for the IP Interface in network byte order.

basRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets.name: basRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets
basRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets.description: The number of RIP response packets received by the RIP process which were subsequently discarded for any reason (e.g. a version 0 packet, or an unknown command type).

basRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes.name: basRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes
basRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes.description: The number of routes, in valid RIP packets, which were ignored for any reason (e.g. unknown address family, or invalid metric).

basRip2IfStatSentUpdates.name: basRip2IfStatSentUpdates
basRip2IfStatSentUpdates.description: The number of triggered RIP updates actually sent on this interface. This explicitly does NOT include full updates sent containing new information.

basRip2IfStatStatus.name: basRip2IfStatStatus
basRip2IfStatStatus.description: Writing invalid has the effect of deleting this interface.

basRip2IfStatChassis.name: basRip2IfStatChassis
basRip2IfStatChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfStatSlot.name: basRip2IfStatSlot
basRip2IfStatSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfStatIf.name: basRip2IfStatIf
basRip2IfStatIf.description: The BAS interface ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfStatLPort.name: basRip2IfStatLPort
basRip2IfStatLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfConfTable.name: basRip2IfConfTable
basRip2IfConfTable.description: A list of subnets which require separate configuration in RIP.

basRip2IfConfEntry.name: basRip2IfConfEntry
basRip2IfConfEntry.description: A Single Routing Domain in a single Subnet.

basRip2IfConfAddress.name: basRip2IfConfAddress
basRip2IfConfAddress.description: The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet. For unnumbered interfaces, the value 0.0.0.N, where the least significant 24 bits (N) is the ifIndex for the IP Interface in network byte order.

basRip2IfConfDomain.name: basRip2IfConfDomain
basRip2IfConfDomain.description: Value inserted into the Routing Domain field of all RIP packets sent on this interface.

basRip2IfConfAuthType.name: basRip2IfConfAuthType
basRip2IfConfAuthType.description: The type of Authentication used on this interface.

basRip2IfConfAuthKey.name: basRip2IfConfAuthKey
basRip2IfConfAuthKey.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key whenever the corresponding instance of rip2IfConfAuthType has a value other than noAuthentication. A modification of the corresponding instance of rip2IfConfAuthType does not modify the rip2IfConfAuthKey value. If a string shorter than 16 octets is supplied, it will be left- justified and padded to 16 octets, on the right, with nulls (0x00). Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

basRip2IfConfSend.name: basRip2IfConfSend
basRip2IfConfSend.description: What the router sends on this interface. ripVersion1 implies sending RIP updates compliant with RFC 1058. rip1Compatible implies broadcasting RIP-2 updates using RFC 1058 route subsumption rules. ripVersion2 implies multicasting RIP-2 updates. ripV1Demand indicates the use of Demand RIP on a WAN interface under RIP Version 1 rules. ripV2Demand indicates the use of Demand RIP on a WAN interface under Version 2 rules.

basRip2IfConfReceive.name: basRip2IfConfReceive
basRip2IfConfReceive.description: This indicates which version of RIP updates are to be accepted. Note that rip2 and rip1OrRip2 implies reception of multicast packets.

basRip2IfConfDefaultMetric.name: basRip2IfConfDefaultMetric
basRip2IfConfDefaultMetric.description: This variable indicates the metric that is to be used for the default route entry in RIP updates originated on this interface. A value of zero indicates that no default route should be originated; in this case, a default route via another router may be propagated.

basRip2IfConfStatus.name: basRip2IfConfStatus
basRip2IfConfStatus.description: Writing invalid has the effect of deleting this interface.

basRip2IfConfSrcAddress.name: basRip2IfConfSrcAddress
basRip2IfConfSrcAddress.description: The IP Address this system will use as a source address on this interface. If it is a numbered interface, this MUST be the same value as rip2IfConfAddress. On unnumbered interfaces, it must be the value of rip2IfConfAddress for some interface on the system.

basRip2IfConfChassis.name: basRip2IfConfChassis
basRip2IfConfChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfConfSlot.name: basRip2IfConfSlot
basRip2IfConfSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfConfIf.name: basRip2IfConfIf
basRip2IfConfIf.description: The BAS interface ID of the Route Server.

basRip2IfConfLPort.name: basRip2IfConfLPort
basRip2IfConfLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of the Route Server.

basRip2PeerEntry.name: basRip2PeerEntry
basRip2PeerEntry.description: Information regarding a single routing peer.

basRip2PeerAddress.name: basRip2PeerAddress
basRip2PeerAddress.description: The IP Address that the peer is using as its source address. Note that on an unnumbered link, this may not be a member of any subnet on the system.

basRip2PeerDomain.name: basRip2PeerDomain
basRip2PeerDomain.description: The value in the Routing Domain field in RIP packets received from the peer. As domain suuport is deprecated, this must be zero.

basRip2PeerLastUpdate.name: basRip2PeerLastUpdate
basRip2PeerLastUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime when the most recent RIP update was received from this system.

basRip2PeerVersion.name: basRip2PeerVersion
basRip2PeerVersion.description: The RIP version number in the header of the last RIP packet received.

basRip2PeerRcvBadPackets.name: basRip2PeerRcvBadPackets
basRip2PeerRcvBadPackets.description: The number of RIP response packets from this peer discarded as invalid.

basRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes.name: basRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes
basRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes.description: The number of routes from this peer that were ignored because the entry format was invalid.

basRip2PeerChassis.name: basRip2PeerChassis
basRip2PeerChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of the Route Server.

basRip2PeerSlot.name: basRip2PeerSlot
basRip2PeerSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of the Route Server.

basRip2PeerIf.name: basRip2PeerIf
basRip2PeerIf.description: The BAS interface ID of the Route Server.

basRip2PeerLPort.name: basRip2PeerLPort
basRip2PeerLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of the Route Server.
